  <summary date="2023-08-28T18:32:29Z" status="Introduced in House">Women in Criminal Justice Reform Act

This bill establishes programs and requirements to address the health and wellness of women in the criminal justice system. For example, the bill requires the Bureau of Prisons to (1) ensure that all incarcerated women have access to basic standards of health care specific to their needs, and (2) develop and implement gender-responsive training for its officers and employees.</summary>
